canonical:
  title: 肅宗封延德宮主爲王妃冊
  author: 無名氏
  language: lzh
  text: 云云殷聘有莘而作配周徵太任以爲妃而致王業之勃興載史編而彪煥合遵舊制特擧寵章咨爾延德宮主李氏霽月儲精曾沙協慶結褵外邸行婦道以有聞鳴珮中闈贊皇猷而匪懈旋被神明之福祐得諧胤嗣之蕃昌今遣某官某持節備禮冊命爲王妃於戱絲綸降命俾正位於璇宮褕翟加儀永流芳於彤管敎訓斯在敬愼勿忘
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 肅宗封延德宮主爲王妃冊
  author: 無名氏
  language: lzh
  text: 云云。殷聘有莘而作配。周徵太任以爲妃。而致王業之勃興。載史編而彪煥。合遵舊制。特擧寵章。咨爾延德宮主李氏。霽月儲精。曾沙協慶。結褵外邸。行婦道以有聞。鳴珮中闈。贊皇猷而匪懈。旋被神明之福祐。得諧胤嗣之蕃昌。今遣某官某。持節備禮。冊命爲王妃。於戱。絲綸降命。俾正位於璇宮。褕翟加儀。永流芳於彤管。敎訓斯在。敬愼勿忘。
korean:
  title: 숙종 봉 연덕궁주 위 왕비 책
  author: 무명씨
  language: kor
  text: 운운. 은(殷)나라에서는 유신씨(有莘氏)를 맞아서 배필을 삼고, 주(周)나라에서는 태임(太任)을 맞아서 비를 삼아, 왕업을 일으키어 사책에 실려 빛이 났다. 그러니 옛 제도를 좇아서 특별히 총애하는 예절을 거행하는 것이 마땅하다.아, 너 연덕궁주(延德宮主) 이씨(李氏)는 제월(霽月)의 정기를 탔고 증사(曾沙)가 경사에 합하였다. 대궐 밖에서 가례(嘉禮)를 행하매 부도(婦道)를 행하여 명성이 있었고, 궁중에서 옥패(玉珮)를 울리매 임금의 덕을 도와서 게을리하지 않았다. 이에 신명(神明)께서 복 주는 것을 받아서 자손이 번창함을 얻었다. 이제 모관 모를 보내어 책명하여 왕비를 삼는다.아, 고명(誥命)을 내리어 왕비의 위에 오르게 하고, 꿩털 옷으로 의식을 갖추어 동관(彤管)에 길이 꽃다움을 전한다. 교훈이 바로 여기에 있으니, 공경하고 조심하여 잊지 말지어다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0310_010_0190&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Imperial Edict Conferring the Status of Royal Consort upon the Lady of Yŏndŏk Palace
  author: Anonymous
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Thus it is written. In ancient Yin, they took a maiden of Youxin as consort and thereby founded their dynasty's glory. In Zhou, they received Taifen as queen and thus brought forth the flowering of royal virtue, their deeds inscribed in the histories and luminous for all ages. Following this precedent of old, we now conduct this ceremony of special honor.

    Hear now, O Lady of Yŏndŏk Palace, Yi of the house Lee: You carry within you the essence of the clear moon, and auspicious signs have aligned with your destiny. When you entered the royal household, you walked the path of wifely virtue with such distinction that your name became known throughout the realm. Within the palace walls, your jade pendants ring with each measured step as you aid the throne's governance without cease. Blessed by divine grace, you have been granted the fortune of bearing heirs to ensure succession.

    Therefore, we now send our appointed officials bearing this sealed decree to elevate you to the rank of Royal Consort. Behold! Through this imperial command, you ascend to the highest station among women. Adorned in the robes of state, your virtues shall be recorded in the annals for all generations to cherish. Let these words of instruction remain ever in your heart: be reverent, be vigilant, and never forget.
  footnotes:
    - 'Youxin (有莘): A noble family whose daughter became consort to the legendary sage-king Yin Tang, exemplifying the classical ideal of a virtuous consort.'
    - 'Taifen (太任): Mother of King Wen of Zhou, celebrated in Confucian tradition as the exemplary royal consort whose virtue influenced the dynasty''s fortune.'
    - 'Yŏndŏk Palace (延德宮): The residence of the prince''s consort or royal family member in Joseon court protocol.'
    - The 'clear moon' and 'auspicious signs' are poetic references to the lady's innate virtue and favorable celestial omens.
    - '彤管 (recorded in the annals): Literally ''red brush,'' a classical reference to women''s virtuous deeds preserved in historical records.'
